1 AN ACT
2 To enact Chapter 15 of Title 51 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950, to be comprised
3 of R.S. 51:1501 through 1504, relative to medical debt protection; to create the
4 Louisiana Medical Debt Protection Act; to provide relative to interest rate
5 limitations; to provide for an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. Chapter 15 of Title 51 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
8 comprised of R.S. 51:1501 through 1504, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 CHAPTER 15. MEDICAL DEBT PROTECTIONS
10 §1501. Short title
11 This Chapter shall be known and may be cited as the "Louisiana
12 Medical Debt Protection Act".
13 §1502. Definitions
14 As used in this Chapter, the following terms have the following
15 meanings:
16 (1) "Medical creditor" means any entity that provides healthcare
17 services and to whom the consumer owes money for healthcare services, or the
18 entity that provided healthcare services and to whom the consumer previously
19 owed money if the medical debt has been purchased by one or more debt
