1 buyers.
2 (2)(a) "Medical debt" means debt arising from healthcare services,
3 including products, devices, durable medical equipment, and prescription
4 drugs, and from the provisions of transportation to healthcare services.
5 (b) "Medical debt" does not include either of the following:
6 (i) An open-end or closed-end extension of credit made by a federally
7 insured financial institution, its subsidiaries, or affiliates.
8 (ii) A debt charged to a credit card.
9 (3) "Medical debt collector" means any person that regularly collects or
10 attempts to collect, directly or indirectly, medical debts originally owed or due
11 or asserted to be owed or due to another. A medical debt buyer shall be
12 considered a medical debt collector for all purposes.
13 (4) "Medically necessary care" means healthcare services, products, or
14 medications that a licensed healthcare provider determines are necessary to
15 prevent, diagnose, or treat an illness, injury, disease, or its symptoms, and that
16 meet accepted standards of care.
17 §1503. Interest rate limitation
18 Interest on medical debt arising from medically necessary care shall not
19 exceed three percent per annum. Any contractual provision imposing a higher
20 rate is void.
21 §1504. Enforcement
22 A. The attorney general may enforce the provisions of this Chapter and
23 seek civil penalties.
24 B. The attorney general shall establish a complaint process whereby an
25 aggrieved consumer or any member of the public may file a complaint against
26 a medical creditor or medical debt collector who violates any provision of this
27 Chapter. All complaints shall be considered public records pursuant to R.S.
28 44:1 et seq., with the exception of the complainant's name, address, or other
29 personal identifying information, which shall be considered confidential and
30 redacted from the complaint.
